      <section class="layout">
        <!-- LEFT: Narrative + key points -->
        <article>
          <h2 class="section-title">Headline summary</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            This profile suggests I’m strongest as a
            <span class="highlight">Resource Investigator</span> and
            <span class="highlight">Monitor Evaluator</span>, with strong
            <span class="highlight">Plant</span>,
            <span class="highlight">Implementer</span> and
            <span class="highlight">Specialist</span> tendencies.
            In plain terms: I like exploring ideas and connections, I think
            things through carefully, and I enjoy turning good ideas into
            practical systems or solutions.
          </p>

          <div class="tag-row">
            <div class="tag"><strong>RE – Resource Investigator</strong> · explorer of ideas & contacts</div>
            <div class="tag"><strong>ME – Monitor Evaluator</strong> · analytical, evaluates options</div>
            <div class="tag"><strong>PL – Plant</strong> · creative problem-solver</div>
            <div class="tag"><strong>IMP – Implementer</strong> · turns plans into action</div>
            <div class="tag"><strong>SP – Specialist</strong> · deep expertise in chosen areas</div>
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">How I tend to add value</h2>
          <div class="subsection">
            <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span><span>Strengths in a team</span></div>
            <h3>Explorer, analyst and builder</h3>
            <p>
              I’m likely to contribute by spotting opportunities, making
              connections across people, tools and ideas, and by questioning
              assumptions so the team makes better decisions. I enjoy
              problem-solving, improving processes and building practical
              solutions, especially in areas where I’ve built up specialist
              knowledge.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="subsection">
            <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span><span>Watch-outs</span></div>
            <h3>Where I may need support</h3>
            <p>
              I’m less naturally drawn to highly forceful “driving” behaviour
              (Shaper) or very fine-grained perfectionism (Completer Finisher).
              I can step into these when needed, but I’m usually at my best
              when paired with people who enjoy pushing deadlines hard and
              polishing outputs to the final detail, while I focus on ideas,
              analysis and implementation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="subsection">
            <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span><span>Working with me</span></div>
            <h3>How others can get the best from me</h3>
            <p>
              I tend to do my best work when I’m involved early in designing
              processes, systems or decisions; when there’s space to explore
              options and think through implications; and when I can help turn
              agreed ideas into something concrete. Clear goals, honest
              discussion and a bit of room for problem-solving usually bring out
              my strengths.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

